properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 18 at 3:01PM CST until February 19 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...HAZARDOUS WIND CHILLS OVERNIGHT ACROSS PORTIONS OF WEST CENTRAL
MINNESOTA...

.Hazardous wind chills of 25 to 30 degrees below zero will are
expected to develop after midnight across portions of west central
Minnesota. Temperatures will improve after sunrise, but hazardous
wind chills are still expected through 9 AM.

* WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as
25 below zero.

* WHERE...Douglas, Todd, Stevens and Pope Counties.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 9 AM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 9 AM CST WEDNESDAY
